OL,3,CNo 10 apologises for serving alcohol
OL,4,Cand meat during Diwali Downing Street
OL,5,Cevent
OL,7,FDowning Street has apologised to
OL,8,FBritish Hindus after it served alcohol
OL,9,Fand meat at a Diwali event hosted at
OL,10,FNumber 10.
OL,12,FAfter facing backlash, Number 10
OL,13,Fadmitted on Friday a "mistake" had
OL,14,Fbeen made in the organisation of the
OL,15,Fevent held on October 29 and sought to
OL,16,Freassure British Hindus that "it will
OL,17,Fnot happen again".
